# CFAI - Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ============================================
# DATABASE
# ============================================
# PostgreSQL connection string
# Local: postgresql://user@localhost:5432/dbname?schema=public
# Vercel Postgres: Will be auto-populated when you connect database
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user@localhost:5432/postgres?schema=public"

# ============================================
# NEXTAUTH (Frontend - apps/web)
# ============================================
# Google OAuth Client ID (from Google Cloud Console)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com"

# Google OAuth Client Secret (from Google Cloud Console)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-google-client-secret"

# NextAuth Secret (generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
# CRITICAL: Must be set in production for session encryption
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-nextauth-secret-here"

# NextAuth URL (your app's public URL)
# Local: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://yourdomain.com
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ============================================
# AI & EXTERNAL APIS (Backend - apps/backend)
# ============================================
# Google AI (Gemini) API Key for stock analysis
# Get from: https://ai.google.dev/
GOOGLE_API_KEY="your-google-ai-api-key"

# Financial Modeling Prep API Key for financial data
# Get from: https://financialmodelingprep.com/developer/docs/
FMP_API_KEY="your-fmp-api-key"

# Financial Modeling Prep Base URL (optional override)
FMP_BASE_URL="https://financialmodelingprep.com/api/v3"

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================
# 
# FOR VERCEL (Frontend - apps/web):
# 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
# 2. Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Add these variables:
#    - DATABASE_URL (from Vercel Postgres)
#    - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
#    - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET
#    - NEXTAUTH_URL (your Vercel domain)
#    - NEXTAUTH_SECRET (generate new for production)
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL (from Motia Cloud)
#
# FOR MOTIA CLOUD (Backend - apps/backend):
# 1. Go to motia.cloud and create an account
# 2. Start local backend: cd apps/backend && pnpm dev
# 3. Navigate to "Import from Workbench"
# 4. Upload .env file or paste these variables:
#    - DATABASE_URL (same Vercel Postgres URL)
#    - GOOGLE_API_KEY
#    - FMP_API_KEY
#    - FMP_BASE_URL
# 5. Click Deploy (Redis auto-configured!)
#
# Alternative: Self-hosted with Railway/Docker
# - See .github/DEPLOYMENT.md for self-hosting guide
# - Requires manual Redis setup
# - More complex but full control
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - Never commit .env to git (already in .gitignore)
# - Generate production NEXTAUTH_SECRET with: openssl rand -base64 32
# - Use different secrets for staging/production
# - Rotate secrets periodically
